  "pages": [
    {
      "page_number": 1,
      "raw_text": "Police Commissioner Tuerke to-\nday said:\n\n\nwith regard to the care of the\nprisoners, we have the situation\nwell in hand. The men at the\nFranklin school were supplied with\nstoves and wood to keep them\nwarm, and consented to take food.\nAt Fort Wright the men agreed to\nwork about their quarters and keep\nthe place clean in consideration of\nreceiving food Later they refused\nto do this work, and concluded to\ngo on hunger strike, and have\ndone so.\n\n\nAT the city jail the situation re.\nmains unchanged. l think the pc.\nlice have the matter well In hand."
    }
